# PRINT REPORT RULES

## Print/Report Method Implementation

### Back Layer Only
- Print methods (GetPrintData) are implemented ONLY in Back layer
- These methods are NOT exposed through Common interfaces

### Class Structure
- **Print Class**: `{ProgramName}PrintCls.cs` - Standalone class (NO inheritance from R_BusinessObjectAsync)
- **Constructor Pattern**: Include Logger and ActivitySource initialization
- **Location**: Same Back project as main business logic class

### Method Naming Convention
- **Back Method**: `GetPrintData()` (NON-ASYNC)
- **Parameter DTO**: `{ProgramName}GetPrintDataParameterDTO`
- **Result DTO**: Use separate `{ProgramName}GetPrintDataResultDTO` (NOT StreamDTO)

### Parameter DTOs
- Create separate parameter DTOs for print operations
- Include all necessary parameters for report generation
- Use same naming convention as other parameter DTOs

### Query and Stored Procedure
- No modifications to SQL queries or stored procedures

## Rules
- Print methods are Back Project-only and Front Project-Only implementations
- Do NOT add print methods to Common interfaces
- Maintain exact stored procedure compatibility
- Print methods MUST be in separate `{ProgramName}PrintCls.cs` class
- Print class MUST include Logger and ActivitySource initialization
- Print methods MUST be NON-ASYNC (synchronous)
- Print methods MUST use separate result DTOs (NOT StreamDTO)

## Violations
- ❌ Adding print methods to Common interfaces
- ❌ Exposing print methods through Service layer
- ❌ Modifying stored procedure names or parameters
- ❌ Using streaming patterns for print operations
- ❌ Print methods in main business logic class
- ❌ Print class without Logger/ActivitySource initialization
- ❌ Making print methods async
- ❌ Using StreamDTO for print results